---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "June 12, 2025";
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - Tech Engineer" showFooter={false}>
  <div class="terms-page">
    <!-- HEADER -->
    <header class="terms-header">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <!-- TABLE OF CONTENTS -->
    <nav class="toc">
      <h3>Contents</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><a href="#acceptance">Acceptance of Terms</a></li>
        <li><a href="#accounts">Account Registration</a></li>
        <li><a href="#guidelines">Community Guidelines</a></li>
        <li><a href="#content">User-Generated Content</a></li>
        <li><a href="#moderation">Moderation & Enforcement</a></li>
        <li><a href="#ip">Intellectual Property</a></li>
        <li><a href="#disclaimer">Disclaimers</a></li>
        <li><a href="#liability">Limitation of Liability</a></li>
        <li><a href="#privacy">Privacy</a></li>
        <li><a href="#changes">Changes to Terms</a></li>
        <li><a href="#contact">Contact Us</a></li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <!-- SECTIONS -->
    <article class="terms-body">
      <section id="acceptance">
        <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using TechEngineer ("the Platform"), you agree to be
          bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to
          these Terms, please do not use the Platform. These Terms apply to all
          visitors, users, and contributors of the Platform.
        </p>
        <p>
          TechEngineer is a community-driven platform where engineers and
          technology professionals can ask questions, share knowledge, join
          Spaces, and engage in discussions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="accounts">
        <h2>2. Account Registration</h2>
        <p>
          To participate in the community (posting, commenting, upvoting,
          joining Spaces), you must create an account. We use third-party
          authentication (Google) to verify your identity.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            You must provide accurate and complete information during
            registration.
          </li>
          <li>
            You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account.
          </li>
          <li>You must be at least 13 years old to create an account.</li>
          <li>
            You may not create multiple accounts for the purpose of manipulating
            content or metrics.
          </li>
          <li>
            You must notify us immediately of any unauthorized use of your
            account.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="guidelines">
        <h2>3. Community Guidelines</h2>
        <p>When using TechEngineer, you agree <strong>not</strong> to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Post content that is offensive, harassing, hateful, or
            discriminatory.
          </li>
          <li>Share misleading, false, or deceptive information.</li>
          <li>
            Post spam, advertisements, or promotional content without context.
          </li>
          <li>Upload malicious code, viruses, or harmful software.</li>
          <li>Impersonate another person or entity.</li>
          <li>
            Engage in vote manipulation (creating fake accounts to upvote your
            own content).
          </li>
          <li>
            Share another user's personal information without their consent
            (doxxing).
          </li>
          <li>
            Post content that violates any applicable local, state, national, or
            international law.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We encourage all members to be respectful, constructive, and helpful.
          Diverse perspectives make our community stronger.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="content">
        <h2>4. User-Generated Content</h2>
        <p>
          You retain ownership of any content you post on TechEngineer,
          including questions, answers, comments, and images. By posting
          content, you grant TechEngineer a <strong
            >non-exclusive, royalty-free, worldwide</strong
          >
          license to use, display, reproduce, and distribute your content within the
          Platform.
        </p>
        <p>You represent and warrant that:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>You own or have the necessary rights to post the content.</li>
          <li>
            Your content does not infringe on any third party's intellectual
            property rights.
          </li>
          <li>Your content complies with these Terms and applicable laws.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          TechEngineer does not claim ownership of your code snippets,
          tutorials, or technical solutions. However, by sharing them publicly,
          you acknowledge that others may use and build upon them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="moderation">
        <h2>5. Moderation & Enforcement</h2>
        <p>
          TechEngineer reserves the right to moderate content and user behavior
          to maintain a healthy community. Actions we may take include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Warning</strong> — For minor first-time violations.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Content Removal</strong> — Deleting posts, comments, or images
            that violate these Terms.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Banning</strong> — Suspending or permanently banning accounts
            for serious or repeated violations.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Space Removal</strong> — Deleting Spaces that violate community
            standards.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Banned users will receive a notification explaining the action. You
          may appeal a ban by contacting us at the email listed below.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="ip">
        <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          The TechEngineer name, logo, design, and all associated branding are
          the intellectual property of TechEngineer and may not be used without
          prior written permission.
        </p>
        <p>
          User-submitted content remains the property of the respective users.
          If you believe your intellectual property has been infringed upon,
          please contact us with:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            A description of the copyrighted work you claim has been infringed.
          </li>
          <li>The URL or location of the allegedly infringing content.</li>
          <li>Your contact information (name, email address).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="disclaimer">
        <h2>7. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>
          TechEngineer is provided on an <strong>"AS IS"</strong> and <strong
            >"AS AVAILABLE"</strong
          > basis. We make no warranties, expressed or implied, regarding the Platform's
          reliability, accuracy, availability, or fitness for a particular purpose.
        </p>
        <p>We do not guarantee that:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The Platform will be uninterrupted or error-free.</li>
          <li>
            Any content, advice, or code found on the Platform is accurate,
            reliable, or safe to use.
          </li>
          <li>Defects or errors will be corrected promptly.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong
            >Use any code, solutions, or advice found on TechEngineer at your
            own risk.</strong
          >
          Always test code in a safe environment before deploying to production.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="liability">
        <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, TechEngineer and its operators
          shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
          consequential, or punitive damages arising from:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your use of or inability to use the Platform.</li>
          <li>
            Any content posted by users, including code, advice, or opinions.
          </li>
          <li>Unauthorized access to your account or personal data.</li>
          <li>
            Any action taken by moderators regarding your content or account.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="privacy">
        <h2>9. Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Your use of TechEngineer is also governed by our Privacy Policy. We
          collect minimal personal information (email, name, profile picture via
          Google authentication) and store it securely on Google's
          infrastructure.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal data to third parties. Your email is used
          solely for authentication, notifications, and account management.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="changes">
        <h2>10. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          TechEngineer reserves the right to update or modify these Terms at any
          time. When we make changes:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            We will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.
          </li>
          <li>
            Significant changes will be communicated via email or a Platform
            notification.
          </li>
          <li>
            Continued use of the Platform after changes constitutes acceptance
            of the new Terms.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We encourage you to review these Terms periodically to stay informed.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="contact">
        <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about these Terms, need to report a violation,
          or wish to appeal a moderation action, please reach out:
        </p>
        <div class="contact-box">
          <p>
            📧 <strong>Email:</strong>
            <a href="mailto:techengineer2026@gmail.com"
              >techengineer2026@gmail.com</a>
          </p>
          <p>🌐 <strong>Platform:</strong> <a href="/">Tech Engineer</a></p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>

    <!-- FOOTER NOTE -->
    <div class="terms-footer">
      <p>
        By using TechEngineer, you acknowledge that you have read, understood,
        and agree to be bound by these Terms of Service.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .terms-page {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 40px 20px 80px;
  }

  /* HEADER */
  .terms-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    padding-bottom: 30px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e3e6ea;
  }
  .terms-header h1 {
    font-size: 36px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  .terms-header p {
    color: #939598;
    font-size: 14px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* TABLE OF CONTENTS */
  .toc {
    background: #f8f9fa;
    border: 1px solid #e3e6ea;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }
  .toc h3 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #636466;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }
  .toc ol {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 20px;
  }
  .toc li {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .toc a {
    color: #2e69ff;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .toc a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* BODY */
  .terms-body section {
    margin-bottom: 36px;
  }
  .terms-body h2 {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    padding-bottom: 8px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #f0f0f0;
  }
  .terms-body p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: #3a3a3a;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }
  .terms-body ul {
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    padding-left: 24px;
  }
  .terms-body li {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: #3a3a3a;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  /* CONTACT BOX */
  .contact-box {
    background: #f8f9fa;
    border: 1px solid #e3e6ea;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }
  .contact-box p {
    margin: 0 0 6px;
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .contact-box p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .contact-box a {
    color: #2e69ff;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .contact-box a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* FOOTER */
  .terms-footer {
    margin-top: 40px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 2px solid #e3e6ea;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .terms-footer p {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #939598;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* RESPONSIVE */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .terms-header h1 {
      font-size: 28px;
    }
    .terms-body h2 {
      font-size: 18px;
    }
    .terms-page {
      padding: 20px 16px 60px;
    }
  }
</style>
